Secretary of Veterans Affairs, David Shulkin, gave a press briefing on the progress and challenges faced by the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA). He discussed 13 areas of significant risk for the VA, including access to care, paying providers, community care, quality of care, disability claims and appeals, information technology, capital assets, construction, accountability, staffing, bureaucracy, fraud, waste, and abuse, and veteran suicides. Shulkin outlined the steps being taken to address these issues, such as improving access to care, modernizing IT systems, and passing new accountability legislation. He also emphasized the need for collaboration with Congress and other organizations to fix the problems within the VA.